# Example Article Three: Building Better Tools

A third mock article for comprehensive testing.

## The Importance of Good Tooling

Good developer tools can significantly improve productivity. The bookmark reader is designed to help you save and organize articles for later reading.

## Features Overview

| Feature | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| Progress Tracking | Saves your scroll position |
| Annotations | Highlight and add notes |
| Read/Unread | Organize by read status |
| Scraping | Add new bookmarks easily |

## Architecture

The bookmark reader uses:

- **Cloudflare Workers** for serverless compute
- **R2** for storing scraped content
- **KV** for user progress and annotations

## Best Practices

1. Always test locally before deploying
2. Use mock data for consistent testing
3. Check all edge cases

## Final Thoughts

Building tools that you actually use yourself is one of the best ways to ensure quality. Happy reading!
